----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Fixed type errors: replaced references to Database, FlightDataAPI, RunwaySlotDB (Interfaces/IfaceKind) with concrete Resource sigs RunwaySlotData and FlightData.
-- Summary 2: Fixed type mismatches in predicates where op.target was compared to op.initiator.mayPerform; changed to op.initiator in op.target.accessible.
-- Summary 3: Adjusted edge case assertions to use RunwaySlotData for ec_safe_1.
-- Summary 4: All invariants, predicates, assertions, and commands are now type-correct and consistent.
-- Assumption 1: RunwaySlotData and FlightData are the concrete resources representing runway slot allocations and flight data respectively.
-- Assumption 2: The interfaces (FlightDataAPI, RunwaySlotDB) are only channels, not targets.
-- Assumption 3: Each Resource must have exactly one owner; this is enforced by the signature declaration.
-- Open issue 1: The ec_safe_3 assertion is vacuously true because every Resource has a mandatory owner; it may not capture incomplete data edge cases.
-- Open issue 2: The ec_safe_4 assertion is vacuously true because every operation has at least one target due to an invariant; it may not effectively test filtering by non-existent runway.
-- Open issue 3: The model lacks explicit representation of runways and time; filtering behavior is approximated via post-states and resources.


